in 1688, but not every bearer of the surname can claim relationship with the royal house, even in Scotland. Every great house in medieval England and Scotland had its steward, and in many cases the office gave rise to a hereditary surname. The fall of the house of Stuart in Britain, conversely, led to the establishment of several highly placed branches bearing this surname in continental Europe, which are in most cases related to the old Scottish royal family."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Conghal Steward of Strathearn was born in 1190, in Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland as the son of Duncan de Tullibardine and Mrs. Duncan de Tullibardine. He had at least 1 daughter with Ada of Catherlavenach."},"et":{"1190–":"1190–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1270–1284":"1270–1284","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1190":"1190","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1190–":"1190–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1270–1284":"1270–1284","1164–Male":"1164–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1190":"1190","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1190–":"1190–Décédé","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1270–1284":"1270–1284","1164–Male":"1164–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1190":"1190","1210":"1210","1164":"1164","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","Tullibardine, Perthshire, Scotland":"Tullibardine, Perthshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Conghal Steward of Strathearn est né en 1190, à Tullibardine, Perthshire, Écosse, fils de Duncan de Tullibardine et Mrs. Duncan de Tullibardine. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Ada of Catherlavenach."},"de":{"1190–":"1190–Verstorben","1190–Male":"1190–Verstorben","1210–Female":"1210–Verstorben","1270–1284":"1270–1284","1164–Male":